      "agentResultText": "Build passes cleanly. Here's a summary of everything that was implemented:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n**New files:**\n- `src/app/api/auth/[slug]/route.ts` — PropelAuth callback route handler (handles login/logout/signup flows)\n- `src/middleware.ts` — Auth middleware that runs on all routes to manage session cookies\n- `src/lib/auth.ts` — `getAuthUser()` helper that validates the session, then upserts the PropelAuth user into the local Prisma database\n- `src/components/nav-bar.tsx` — Client component with auth-aware navigation (shows login/signup when logged out, email + logout when logged in)\n\n**Modified files:**\n- `prisma/schema.prisma` — Added `propelAuthId String @unique` to the `User` model\n- `prisma/seed.js` — Added placeholder `propelAuthId` for the seed user\n- `src/app/layout.tsx` — Wrapped app in `AuthProvider`, replaced static nav with `NavBar` component\n- `src/app/dashboard/page.tsx` — Uses `getAuthUser()` to scope posts to the logged-in user\n- `src/app/dashboard/actions.ts` — All CRUD actions now authenticate the user and scope queries to their `authorId`\n- `src/app/settings/page.tsx` — Loads profile from the authenticated user\n- `src/app/settings/actions.ts` — Updates the authenticated user's profile\n\n**How it works:**\n1. The middleware manages PropelAuth session cookies on every request\n2. `AuthProvider` gives client components access to user state via `useUser()`\n3. Protected pages (`/dashboard`, `/settings`) call `getAuthUser()` which redirects to PropelAuth's hosted login page if not authenticated\n4. On first login, the user is automatically created in the local database via `upsert`\n5. All data operations are scoped to the authenticated user's ID",
