      "agentResultText": "Build passes. Here's what changed:\n\n**`src/middleware.ts`** — Switched from bare `authMiddleware` to `buildAuthMiddleware` with an `afterAuthHook`. When an unauthenticated user hits `/dashboard` or `/settings` (or any sub-path), the middleware redirects them to `/login`.\n\n**`src/lib/auth.ts`** — Switched from `getUserOrRedirect()` (which redirects to PropelAuth's hosted login) to `getUser()` + `redirect(\"/login\")`. This ensures server components also redirect to our custom `/login` page as a fallback.\n\nProtection is now two layers deep:\n1. **Middleware** — catches unauthenticated requests at the edge before the page even renders\n2. **`getAuthUser()`** — server-side guard in each protected page/action as a safety net",
