      "agentResultText": "Build passes. Here's a summary of the auth protection layers now in place:\n\n**Sign-out button** — Already present in the nav bar header via `useLogoutFunction()`. Shows \"Log out\" with the user's email when authenticated, \"Log in\" / \"Sign up\" when not. Visible on every page.\n\n**Session expiry handling** — Added a `useEffect` in the nav bar that monitors auth state. When PropelAuth's `useUser()` detects the session has expired (user becomes `undefined` after being logged in) while on `/dashboard` or `/settings`, it redirects to `/login`. The `wasLoggedIn` ref prevents false redirects on initial page load for public pages.\n\n**Three layers of protection:**\n1. **Middleware** — Blocks unauthenticated requests to `/dashboard` and `/settings` at the edge, redirects to `/login`\n2. **Server components** — `getAuthUser()` calls `getUser()` and redirects to `/login` if no session\n3. **Client-side** — Nav bar detects session expiry and redirects away from protected pages",
